Secure and Encrypted REST API Using RSA Authentication

  1. [GET][SERVER_URL]/rsa/pem/public : to get public_key.pem
  2. [GET][SERVER_URL]/rsa/encrypt/[string:data] : to encrypt data
  3. [GET][SERVER_URL]/web/login/rsa/[string:rsa_token] : to login using rsa token
  4. [GET][SERVER_URL]/rsa/api/v1/dbname : get database name
  5. [POST,GET][SERVER_URL]/rsa/api/v1/signup : sign up api
  6. [POST,GET][SERVER_URL]/rsa/api/v1/oauth2 : oauth2 compatible api
  7. [PATCH][SERVER_URL]/rsa/api/v1/[model_name]/[method] : to execute model method

To get rsa_token, get public key (point number 1 above), do data = '%s:%s' % (username,password) then encrypt data with RSA method, or do point number 6 (more secure), or do point number 2 (less secure).
